Class GabotoBean

java.lang.Object
  org.oucs.gaboto.beans.GabotoBean
All Implemented Interfaces:
RDFContainer
Direct Known Subclasses:
Address, Location
public abstract class GabotoBean
extends java.lang.Object
implements RDFContainer

GabotoBeans are used to allow the storage of complex properties in GabotoEntitys.

GabotoBeans should generally be simple classes following the principles of JavaBeans (see Wikipedia article). The only two a bit more complex methods an GabotoBean has to provide is one method to generate RDF Triples (getCorrespondingRDFTriples(Node) and one to load itself from an RDF resource (#loadFromResource(Resource)).

Author:
Arno Mittelbach

getCorrespondingRDFTriples

public java.util.List<com.hp.hpl.jena.graph.Triple> getCorrespondingRDFTriples(com.hp.hpl.jena.graph.Node blankNode)
Create RDF triples that contain all the information stored in this object.

RDF triples for GabotoBeans will always be of the form: 

  oxpdata:subject               somevocab:definedPredicate              _blankNode .
  _blankNode                    somevocab:predicate1                    "some value";
                                        somevocab:predicate2                    someReference;
                                                ...                                                             ...              .
The first triple is created automatically. It is the beans obligation to create all other necessary "information triples".

Parameters:
blankNode - The blank node to attach information to.
Returns:
A list of RDF triples.

public void loadFromResource(com.hp.hpl.jena.rdf.model.Resource res,
                             GabotoSnapshot snapshot,

Load all information necessary for this GabotoBean from an RDF resource.

In order to automatically load GabotoEntitys beans have to know how their information is stored in RDF and be able to load this information into its fields.

Parameters:
res - The RDF resource containing the information to load this GabotoBean.
